race.comment: SASS APPEAL (14) impressed on debut last start, finishing second over 1200m at Sandown-Lakeside in tougher company. She has plenty of upside and is the one to beat at this level. FOREVER JO (12) made her debut in the same race as the top pick 2-and-a-half weeks ago, finishing fifth over 1200m at Sandown-Lakeside, just over 2 lengths from lengths off the winner. She should naturally improve and can figure in the top 3 this time. ALGORITHMIC (1) is a 5-start maiden who resumed last time out with a seventh over 1200m at Sandown-Lakeside 18 days ago. The extra 200m will suit him, and he gets a chance to live up to that good breeding of his. STORMING CAMELOT (7) finished third here 10 days ago when making his debut, and the quick backup is always a good sign. Stick with him. TRANSPACIFIC (9) resumes from a spell, and is worth including in all top 4 combos.
